I do not at all desire to · see Verse Composition a sine qua non, or to limit even these Examinations to linguistic excellence. Stil] more should ”I lament the failure of the attempts now being made at Cambridge to extend the scope of the Classical T ripos Examination, so as to test power of thought as well as power of expression.
